WEBVTT

00:01.680 --> 00:03.760
Okay, Lily, ballet at 11:00,

00:03.870 --> 00:06.250
then a playdate,
then karate class at 3:00,

00:06.310 --> 00:07.770
so why don't you go get
your uniform?

00:07.880 --> 00:08.770
[ Singsongy ] Chop chop!

00:08.870 --> 00:09.790
<i>- Cam.</i>
- What?

00:09.890 --> 00:11.340
She's in karate.
It's not offensive.

00:11.500 --> 00:14.020
Debatable, but why would you
schedule all this extra stuff

00:14.110 --> 00:15.560
on the same day
as her talent show?

00:15.640 --> 00:17.690
Okay, are you accusing me
of overscheduling

00:17.790 --> 00:19.300
our tone-deaf daughter
so she's so tired

00:19.380 --> 00:22.330
she misses the talent show
and doesn't humiliate herself?

00:22.600 --> 00:23.600
Lily has no talent.

00:23.710 --> 00:26.460
Because she's 7.
No one has talent at 7.

00:26.550 --> 00:28.600
I did. Tons of it.

00:28.700 --> 00:31.040
Sheep-shearing,
cornhusking, hay-baling.

00:31.120 --> 00:33.020
It was hard for me to pick
just one to showcase

00:33.110 --> 00:34.290
at my first little prince
pageant.

00:34.380 --> 00:35.940
In the end,
I went with waltzing.

00:36.030 --> 00:37.320
You waltzed at 7?

00:37.390 --> 00:40.080
Barely. My partner
had two left hooves. Hmm.

00:40.430 --> 00:41.590
[ Singsongy ] I got it!

00:41.720 --> 00:43.830
[ Normal voice ] Hey, wait.
Isn't my talent show today?

00:43.910 --> 00:46.080
Oh, who knows?
But let's go ride some ponies.

00:46.160 --> 00:47.290
No, no, you're right.
It is today,

00:47.370 --> 00:49.420
and since you have a little bit
of time before ballet...

00:49.560 --> 00:51.920
why don't you two
do a little bit of warming up?

00:52.000 --> 00:52.820
Maestro? Come on.

00:52.900 --> 00:54.480
- Oh, okay, great. Thank you.
- Yeah, yeah.

00:54.610 --> 00:57.150
So, Lily, can you
meet me here at...

00:57.230 --> 00:58.150
♪ C? ♪
[ Plays C key ]

00:58.230 --> 01:01.900
[ Off-key ] ♪ C ♪
♪ now daddy's lonely ♪

01:01.980 --> 01:03.250
♪ I'm there with you ♪

01:03.330 --> 01:05.640
♪ no, you're not,
you're not even close ♪

01:05.720 --> 01:08.300
♪ this can't possibly
sound the same to you ♪

01:08.380 --> 01:10.700
♪ Maybe I can help,
daddy is also here at... ♪

01:10.810 --> 01:12.400
Both: ♪ C ♪

01:12.470 --> 01:13.260
[ Off-key ] ♪ C ♪

01:13.340 --> 01:14.990
♪ No, that's not even a note ♪

01:15.090 --> 01:17.050
♪ I feel like you're doing it
on purpose ♪

01:17.140 --> 01:18.440
♪ That seems
a little bit sharp ♪

01:18.530 --> 01:21.240
♪ I'm never sharp,
I'm pitch-perfect ♪

01:21.310 --> 01:22.980
♪ I'm talking about your tone
toward our daughter ♪

01:23.050 --> 01:26.310
♪ I can understand you
even when you're singing ♪

01:39.660 --> 01:40.730
_

01:43.100 --> 01:44.140
What are you doing?

01:44.270 --> 01:48.190
I am gathering every binky
that is in this house,

01:48.320 --> 01:53.180
because from today on,
Joe is going cold turkey.

01:53.820 --> 01:57.700
Okay, Joe, have your last puff
if you want.

01:57.770 --> 01:59.620
Gloria, I'm trying
to watch something here.

01:59.740 --> 02:00.780
[ Sighs ]

02:00.880 --> 02:02.660
Okay, you can keep crying
all you want.

02:02.740 --> 02:05.750
I can't hear anything.
Try growing up in Colombia.

02:05.830 --> 02:08.539
My binky was a spark plug.

02:08.949 --> 02:10.430
Luke, how could you forget
your bathing suit?

02:10.520 --> 02:11.760
You came over here to swim.

02:11.880 --> 02:13.220
It's all right, honey.
He can wear mine.

02:13.320 --> 02:14.480
I'll borrow from Jay.

02:14.570 --> 02:16.770
You have a favorite I should
keep my hands off of, Jay?

02:16.850 --> 02:18.550
That ship sailed
about 20 years ago.

02:18.650 --> 02:20.140
Ha ha! Zinger!

02:20.490 --> 02:21.440
Save some of that charm

02:21.520 --> 02:23.160
for our commercial shoot
today, dad, huh?

02:23.250 --> 02:26.930
Women: <i> ♪ closets, closets,</i>
<i>closets, closets ♪</i>

02:27.340 --> 02:28.980
You see what
our competition's doing?

02:29.070 --> 02:30.360
See the lasers?
Special effects?

02:30.440 --> 02:32.200
I'll bet they spent
5 million bucks on that thing.

02:32.300 --> 02:34.110
Don't worry, dad.
The concept I came up with

02:34.160 --> 02:36.030
- is so much better than theirs.
- We're scrapping it.

02:36.130 --> 02:37.600
What? I worked
for two months on that.

02:37.710 --> 02:39.590
Sorry. We gotta go
with what's proven.

02:39.700 --> 02:41.810
We're remaking
my old commercial.

02:41.920 --> 02:43.890
30 years ago,
my dad was in a local ad

02:43.970 --> 02:46.020
for Pritchett's Closets,
and he has always been

02:46.100 --> 02:48.530
really proud of the slogan
he came up with.

02:49.720 --> 02:51.450
I've never understood
what it means.

02:51.540 --> 02:52.900
<i>[ 1980s-style instrumental music
playing ] Man: Pritchett's Closets--</i>

02:53.000 --> 02:54.970
<i>choose one</i>
<i>of our nine luxurious models</i>

02:55.100 --> 02:56.540
<i>like the Monte Carlo.</i>

02:56.650 --> 02:58.130
<i>Or how about a custom design</i>

02:58.230 --> 03:00.500
<i>using our state-of-the-art</i>
<i>technology?</i>

03:00.650 --> 03:02.040
<i>Come visit Pritchett's</i>

03:02.120 --> 03:04.740
<i>and go home</i>
<i>with the closet of your dreams.</i>

03:04.900 --> 03:07.490
Closet? You'll love it!

03:08.330 --> 03:11.450
[ Chuckles ] The entire town
went nuts for that ad.

03:11.540 --> 03:12.590
People stopped me
in the street,

03:12.690 --> 03:14.500
asking me to say the slogan.

03:14.620 --> 03:16.520
Are you sure they weren't
asking you to explain it?

03:16.600 --> 03:17.560
What's to explain?

03:17.620 --> 03:18.760
Instead of "Like it?
You'll love it,"

03:18.840 --> 03:20.080
you use the word "Closet."

03:20.160 --> 03:21.660
Then why not, "Like it?
You'll closet!"?

03:21.760 --> 03:23.340
That makes no sense.

03:23.660 --> 03:25.840
Look, I know it was rough
on you and Mitch

03:25.930 --> 03:26.990
having a famous dad,

03:27.070 --> 03:28.730
you know, getting your picture
taken in restaurants.

03:28.800 --> 03:30.590
That happened one time, dad,
only because we were eating

03:30.670 --> 03:32.740
with Ralph Berman,
"Garage Door Opener King."

03:32.820 --> 03:34.440
Hey, he was eating with <i> us.</i>

03:34.580 --> 03:36.030
- [ Sighs ]
- The point is,

03:36.150 --> 03:38.770
that ad scored for us,
and it will again.

03:38.840 --> 03:40.470
So we're gonna flush
all my hard work

03:40.560 --> 03:42.190
because you got freaked out
by some commercial

03:42.300 --> 03:43.550
that's not even that catchy.

03:43.680 --> 03:46.590
[ Humming ]
♪ closets, closets ♪

03:48.390 --> 03:50.760
All right, get there!

03:52.120 --> 03:52.980
Ugh!

03:53.060 --> 03:55.050
Hey, if you really wanna impress
Beth when she gets here,

03:55.150 --> 03:56.970
you should try
for that giant elephant.

03:57.280 --> 03:59.050
Oh, penguin's just as good.

04:01.680 --> 04:02.340
[ Ball bounces ]

04:02.460 --> 04:03.810
- Money!
- Aah!

04:04.010 --> 04:06.800
I just spent
a lot of money. A lot.

04:06.880 --> 04:08.470
Sorry. I had to check in
at the job.

04:08.570 --> 04:09.940
Always something going down
at The Hut.

04:10.090 --> 04:12.890
You were at The Hut?
I would guess pizza,

04:12.980 --> 04:14.640
but based
on your ripply stomach I saw

04:14.730 --> 04:16.450
when you helped me get down
off the gondola ride,

04:16.519 --> 04:18.420
I'm gonna guess...
Sunglass Hut.

04:18.519 --> 04:20.480
Yep, chase picked out
these vintage-y sunglasses

04:20.630 --> 04:21.920
that look like
I could've been murdered

04:22.010 --> 04:23.660
at a cool house party
in the '70s.

04:23.770 --> 04:25.440
Ooh, you've been <i> framed.</i>

04:25.530 --> 04:27.400
[ Laughs ]
You should use that.

04:27.560 --> 04:29.340
- Hmm?
- At your job at The Hut.

04:29.450 --> 04:31.190
[ Laughs ] You just said
"Jabba the hut."

04:31.310 --> 04:32.830
I'm really lost here, guys.

04:32.920 --> 04:35.530
Oh!
Oh! That smarts.

04:35.620 --> 04:39.300
- Again? - Yeah. Uh, it's probably
just motion sickness.

04:39.390 --> 04:41.410
Uh, yeah, the motion of shoving
deep fried garbage

04:41.500 --> 04:42.800
in your mouth all day.

04:42.910 --> 04:45.140
It's my manager again.
She's always on me.

04:45.250 --> 04:47.490
Can't wait till the fall
when she's off to college.

04:47.700 --> 04:48.970
Yeah, Maureen?

04:49.110 --> 04:50.520
[ Groans ]

04:51.090 --> 04:52.160
Beth's not coming.

04:52.350 --> 04:54.650
She's too tired to drive up
from San Diego.

04:54.890 --> 04:57.780
So this Beth, who I've
never actually met,

04:57.870 --> 05:00.400
is she one of those
real-life move-around girls?

05:00.490 --> 05:03.240
Ha ha.
You know she's a real girl.

05:03.360 --> 05:06.200
<i>Fine,</i> but, you know,
she flew all the way over here

05:06.290 --> 05:07.880
for some coast guard training.

05:07.940 --> 05:09.750
She can't drive a couple hours
to see you?

05:09.830 --> 05:11.650
She's been saving
drowning mannequins all morning,

05:11.780 --> 05:13.530
and some of them
are plus-sized,

05:13.620 --> 05:15.610
because a lot of people
fall off cruise ships.

05:15.730 --> 05:18.010
<i>Okay,</i> but doesn't it bother you

05:18.100 --> 05:20.510
that she's flaked for, like,
the hundredth time?

05:20.630 --> 05:22.170
I know you have a problem
with Beth,

05:22.260 --> 05:25.410
but what we have works
for me, okay?

05:25.500 --> 05:26.750
And if we're pointing fingers...

05:26.820 --> 05:30.170
I want <i> you</i> to help <i> me</i>
find my keys.

05:30.250 --> 05:31.570
Wait. Shh.

05:31.630 --> 05:32.910
- They're in my jacket.
- Okay.

05:32.990 --> 05:34.280
Got it.

05:34.440 --> 05:35.770
[ Whirring ]

05:36.610 --> 05:38.810
Mom, that perv
is ogling you again.

05:38.870 --> 05:41.160
No! I was reading
my horoscope.

05:41.250 --> 05:43.810
"You will borrow
a huge swimsuit today." What?

05:43.950 --> 05:49.070
<i>Ay,</i> no, the plane! The plane!
It's always spying on me!

05:49.170 --> 05:51.600
Go away or I'm gonna call
the policeman!

05:51.680 --> 05:53.930
Wow, don't even waste
your time, Gloria.

05:54.010 --> 05:55.750
Johnny law's got no chance
with that baby.

05:55.910 --> 05:57.230
You're looking
at a freeling cloudgazer

05:57.300 --> 06:00.000
with after-market frequency
scrambler. Untraceable.

06:00.090 --> 06:01.810
As you can guess,
I'm a droner myself.

06:01.890 --> 06:05.770
Yes, you're droning right now.
<i>Ay,</i> it's getting closer!

06:05.840 --> 06:06.980
Mom, maybe you should cover up.

06:07.060 --> 06:09.480
No! That's crazy. We can just
knock it out of the sky.

06:09.560 --> 06:11.060
Manny, grab the hose.

06:12.540 --> 06:13.960
I'll use this to blind it.

06:14.620 --> 06:15.640
My eyes!

06:15.850 --> 06:17.730
- My eyes!
- Oh!

06:17.810 --> 06:20.070
- Oh!
- [ High-pitched voice ] Aah!

06:21.110 --> 06:21.960
[ Whirs ]

06:23.310 --> 06:25.700
And just like that,
it disappears.

06:26.000 --> 06:28.670
In his defense,
the water's really cold.

06:32.510 --> 06:34.900
- [ Speaks indistinctly ]
- Oh! You're still rehearsing.

06:34.990 --> 06:36.970
We sure are, and we found
a more appropriate song

06:37.060 --> 06:38.460
for lily's singing voice.

06:38.590 --> 06:41.220
- Really? Well, I'd love to hear it.
- Okay.

06:42.160 --> 06:45.310
♪ Everybody was
kung fu fighting ♪

06:45.400 --> 06:46.700
Hyah! Hyah!

06:46.790 --> 06:48.660
♪ Those kicks were
fast as lightning ♪

06:48.780 --> 06:50.490
Hyah! Hyah!

06:50.550 --> 06:52.340
♪ In fact, it was
a little bit frightening ♪

06:52.430 --> 06:55.450
Okay, stop, stop, stop.
No, come on. No. No!

06:56.050 --> 06:58.130
This is ridiculous.
She's not even singing.

06:58.270 --> 07:00.050
She wasn't singing before
either.

07:00.220 --> 07:03.280
Okay, go get some water.<i> Cam.</i>

07:03.390 --> 07:04.870
Mitchell, I just don't want her
to embarrass herself

07:04.980 --> 07:08.280
in front of her friends,
not to mention the parents.

07:08.370 --> 07:11.180
I can already hear
Andrew's condescending, "Hmm."

07:11.250 --> 07:13.550
Oh, my gosh. You're still
competing with Andrew.

07:13.660 --> 07:15.460
He staged a coup, Mitchell.

07:15.570 --> 07:17.570
He forced me out of the group
I founded.

07:17.690 --> 07:19.810
I founded it.
The Greensleevers were

07:19.900 --> 07:22.340
Southern California's
premier holiday chorus

07:22.410 --> 07:24.550
and "Just the nutmeg we want

07:24.650 --> 07:26.890
our yuletide eggnog
dusted with"--

07:26.990 --> 07:29.210
- "LA Times," December 23, 199--
- I remember.

07:29.330 --> 07:31.820
<i>Oh,</i> I remember.
I remember.

07:31.900 --> 07:33.550
So you're not worried about
Lily embarrassing herself.

07:33.680 --> 07:35.450
You're worried about
Lily embarrassing <i> you.</i>

07:35.540 --> 07:37.150
Not so much now that
she's not singing.

07:37.690 --> 07:40.860
Hey. Lily is gonna sing
whatever she wants,

07:40.990 --> 07:42.830
and you're gonna get over
this thing with Andrew...

07:42.940 --> 07:44.920
because a grown man
should not have a nemesis.

07:45.010 --> 07:46.390
- It's ridiculous.
- You know what's ridiculous?

07:46.510 --> 07:48.270
Is being forced to turn in
your jingle bells

07:48.360 --> 07:51.260
to a man with less
vocal range than a teakettle.

07:52.690 --> 07:53.890
Hyah!

07:54.440 --> 07:57.830
- [ Crying ]
- [ Footsteps approach ]

07:57.900 --> 07:58.750
Hi.

07:58.830 --> 08:00.230
Oh, I thought you had a date.

08:00.350 --> 08:03.730
I did, but I bailed. He's not
exactly the sharpest shed.

08:03.850 --> 08:05.090
What is <i> his</i> deal?

08:05.210 --> 08:07.330
I took his pacifier hours ago,

08:07.420 --> 08:10.290
and he's still crying.
He's being such a baby.

08:10.380 --> 08:12.110
Well, maybe he's just not
ready to give them up.

08:12.210 --> 08:15.150
No, I promised my mother
that he wouldn't use it anymore.

08:15.280 --> 08:17.520
Her uncle used it
until he was 4,

08:17.620 --> 08:18.690
and now he's in jail.

08:18.780 --> 08:20.900
I feel like a lot of your family
stories end that way.

08:21.020 --> 08:22.940
I'm gonna put on
a bathing suit.

08:23.160 --> 08:24.580
- [ Crying continues ]
- Hi, Manny.

08:24.680 --> 08:26.410
Please stick Joe in front
of the TV.

08:26.510 --> 08:28.250
He always calms down
when he listens to...

08:28.350 --> 08:30.880
♪ Closets, closets,
closets, closets ♪

08:30.960 --> 08:33.559
- Dad, you might wanna see this.
- [ Clicks button ]

08:33.730 --> 08:35.090
<i>Oh!</i>

08:36.470 --> 08:37.870
<i>[ Water splashes,</i>
<i>pool skimmer clanks ]</i>

08:37.950 --> 08:39.280
He put us on YouTube?

08:39.360 --> 08:41.789
He called it
"Drone 1, Idiots 0."

08:41.860 --> 08:43.620
It has 32,000 views.

08:44.540 --> 08:46.080
We have to strike back.

08:46.210 --> 08:48.720
That drone just messed
with the wrong idiot.

08:49.160 --> 08:50.550
- [ Cell phone chimes ]
- [ Sighs ]

08:51.720 --> 08:52.890
[ Gasps ]

08:52.990 --> 08:54.730
Andy's in the hospital.

08:54.810 --> 08:55.920
What? Why?

08:55.990 --> 08:57.420
Appendicitis.

08:57.560 --> 09:00.740
Is he okay? Maybe I should
go down there.

09:00.830 --> 09:02.030
This is not good.

09:02.110 --> 09:04.310
My second cousin
got appendicitis,

09:04.390 --> 09:06.300
and now he's in jail.

09:07.220 --> 09:08.520
Hmm.

09:09.430 --> 09:11.830
Closet? You'll love it.

09:12.590 --> 09:14.190
Man: And... cut.

09:15.010 --> 09:16.020
Uh, that was great, Jay.

09:16.100 --> 09:18.180
Let's try it again.
Maybe a little lighter.

09:18.260 --> 09:19.500
- Lighter.
- Yeah.

09:19.590 --> 09:21.440
Just, you know,
happier, warmer.

09:21.560 --> 09:25.190
Even more? All right.

09:26.020 --> 09:28.500
From Jay's line.
Here we go. And...

09:29.350 --> 09:30.260
action.

09:30.370 --> 09:32.370
Closet? You'll love it!

09:32.500 --> 09:33.240
Cut.

09:33.330 --> 09:35.400
- You see that was exactly
the same, right? - I do.

09:35.490 --> 09:36.770
- So what does it mean?
- I don't know.

09:36.900 --> 09:38.230
- So do we have it?
- Um...

09:38.310 --> 09:39.980
I gave you, like,
10 different choices.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.790
Let's not overthink this, huh?
Just pick one.

09:42.920 --> 09:44.670
Okay. Well... give him a minute.

09:44.760 --> 09:45.740
- He'll calm down.
- Sure.

09:45.830 --> 09:47.270
- Uh, hey, Claire?
- Yes. Yeah.

09:47.330 --> 09:48.390
So we were just talking,

09:48.510 --> 09:51.300
and strictly
from a marketing standpoint,

09:51.390 --> 09:53.710
- do you think Jay is, um...
- He stinks.

09:53.810 --> 09:55.130
- He's the worst. So bad.
- [ Grunts ]

09:55.290 --> 09:59.280
And, um... strictly from
a keeping-my-job standpoint,

09:59.370 --> 10:01.880
it would be so dope
if you told him that.

10:01.970 --> 10:05.260
Oh. Oh, God.
I can't fire my dad!

10:05.350 --> 10:06.500
I know.
I know. It must be hard,

10:06.600 --> 10:08.750
but you realize it's
the best thing for the company.

10:08.830 --> 10:10.190
- Yes, I do.
- Okay.

10:10.270 --> 10:11.550
Can I at least count on you
to back me up?

10:11.650 --> 10:14.500
Totally. Come on. We both
know your dad is incredible.

10:14.560 --> 10:15.890
Do you see him today?
He's like George Clooney

10:15.970 --> 10:17.260
but older, but better.

10:17.320 --> 10:19.320
I...
thought that was Jay. I'm sorry.

10:19.430 --> 10:22.790
Oh, man. Almost fainted.
[ Exhales ]

10:23.440 --> 10:25.040
Just gonna put my head
between my legs.

10:25.180 --> 10:27.000
- Plenty of room down there.
- [ Chuckles nervously ]

10:27.390 --> 10:28.510
[ Pop ]

10:28.590 --> 10:30.630
[ Cheers and applause ]

10:30.790 --> 10:32.430
We'll now take a break
to sweep up the confetti

10:32.530 --> 10:35.560
that was definitely <i> not</i>
mentioned in dress rehearsal.

10:36.030 --> 10:37.410
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:37.690 --> 10:40.400
Okay, here comes Andrew.
Just act like we don't care

10:40.480 --> 10:41.970
about the whole Greensleevers
thing.

10:42.070 --> 10:43.540
Ooh, I hope I could
pull this off.

10:43.900 --> 10:45.070
Cameron.

10:45.150 --> 10:47.270
- Andrew.
- Enjoyable show.

10:47.360 --> 10:50.060
- So did you...
- Direct? No, not this year.

10:50.180 --> 10:51.330
Ah, I didn't think so.

10:51.410 --> 10:52.700
You're...

10:52.780 --> 10:54.000
So we're really enjoying
the show, too.

10:54.170 --> 10:55.710
It's all about the kids,
you know.

10:55.870 --> 10:57.890
Sorry.
They only had flat.

10:58.040 --> 11:00.110
<i>Mitchell.</i>

11:00.310 --> 11:01.550
<i>Simon.</i>

11:01.740 --> 11:05.300
Turns out recently,
Andrew married Simon.

11:05.420 --> 11:07.030
My bitter rival
from law school.

11:07.120 --> 11:08.580
Or... nemesis?

11:08.670 --> 11:09.740
I've...
[ Groans ]

11:09.850 --> 11:12.500
So how's work? I'm sure
you heard I made partner

11:12.600 --> 11:15.010
at Gotshal, Manges,
Flom, Arps, & Leboeuf.

11:15.110 --> 11:17.490
And I'm actually at
the justice institute now.

11:17.590 --> 11:18.700
So rewarding.

11:18.800 --> 11:21.730
Oh, I think our firm donated
one of our old fax machines

11:21.820 --> 11:23.640
to you guys.

11:24.100 --> 11:24.890
♪

11:24.970 --> 11:26.250
We better go.
We're moving closer

11:26.330 --> 11:28.300
because our daughter's
about to perform.

11:28.410 --> 11:30.800
- Yours is from Vietnam, right?
- Mm-hmm.

11:30.880 --> 11:33.250
We were able to adopt one
from Korea.

11:33.410 --> 11:35.460
So...

11:37.390 --> 11:40.160
Did he really just end
a conversation on <i> "So..."?</i>

11:40.250 --> 11:41.300
Let's just take our seats.

11:41.370 --> 11:42.900
No, Cam,
I-I don't know if this is

11:42.980 --> 11:44.720
the most supportive environment
for Lily to--

11:44.820 --> 11:46.440
- I agree. Let's get her out of the show.
- Okay. Yeah.

11:46.520 --> 11:47.960
And are Koreans really better?

11:48.040 --> 11:49.200
I don't know.

11:49.750 --> 11:52.110
[ Drone whirring ]

11:52.180 --> 11:54.830
Chicken's in the pot. I repeat,
we have eyes on the chicken.

11:57.430 --> 11:59.900
Eat paint.
Damn it. I missed.

11:59.970 --> 12:00.970
Luke, gravity!

12:01.050 --> 12:03.510
Shut up, nerd! Ow! Ow!

12:03.560 --> 12:06.040
Plan "B"! If you can't beat 'em,
drone 'em!

12:06.130 --> 12:07.130
Activate voice control!

12:07.230 --> 12:08.310
[ Whirring ]

12:08.370 --> 12:09.740
Forward 10 feet.

12:10.670 --> 12:12.510
- Oh! It's attacking!
- Get down!

12:13.490 --> 12:15.990
Damn it.
Deactivate voice control!

12:16.080 --> 12:19.170
Plan "C"! Follow it home!

12:21.800 --> 12:22.950
Hurry up!

12:23.320 --> 12:25.430
Hey! That's my bike!

12:25.570 --> 12:28.610
We're all making sacrifices!
I'm wearing a monokini!

12:28.700 --> 12:30.390
- Hey, Lizzie! Whoa!
- Aah!

12:30.480 --> 12:31.800
Okay, I need to borrow this,
okay?

12:31.910 --> 12:34.180
Here, just-- all right.
Okay.

12:34.280 --> 12:35.510
I promise to bring it back,
all right?

12:35.630 --> 12:38.800
No, that's what you said
about my mom's humidifier!

12:39.180 --> 12:40.010
[ Drone whirring ]

12:40.510 --> 12:42.250
He's heading for the river
to try and lose us.

12:42.360 --> 12:44.180
Damn you, Denise,
at the patent office

12:44.280 --> 12:46.080
for stalling my aquabike!

12:47.080 --> 12:47.920
Look out!

12:48.020 --> 12:48.670
Ow!

12:50.060 --> 12:50.940
You okay?

12:51.010 --> 12:52.670
It's gonna take more
than a little truck to st--

12:52.760 --> 12:54.010
All: Aah!

12:54.110 --> 12:55.760
- Ohh!
- Ow!

12:57.270 --> 12:59.390
- Ow. Are you guys okay?
- Yeah.

12:59.610 --> 13:01.410
This isn't over yet!
You know that!

13:01.490 --> 13:02.640
- Aah!
- Oh, God! Dad!

13:02.710 --> 13:03.740
Aah! Phil!

13:06.690 --> 13:08.710
<i>- Ohh!</i>
<i>- Ow! Ow! Ow!</i>

13:11.730 --> 13:13.670
"Drone 2, Idiots 0."

13:13.760 --> 13:14.720
Come on!

13:15.050 --> 13:17.870
At least it's far away
so you can't tell it's us.

13:17.980 --> 13:19.140
- Yeah.
- [ Computer bloops ]

13:19.220 --> 13:20.750
Oh, great. Another comment.

13:20.850 --> 13:23.060
"LOL. That's my realtor,
Phil D--"

13:24.430 --> 13:25.700
Okay, let's just grab her
and go.

13:25.770 --> 13:27.010
She's up after the next act.

13:27.100 --> 13:28.200
Hey, we're doing
the right thing.

13:28.300 --> 13:30.370
You can develop
deep emotional scars at age 7.

13:30.480 --> 13:31.400
I still can't eat--

13:31.480 --> 13:32.870
Salt and vinegar chips.
Yes, I know.

13:32.970 --> 13:34.570
I can't relive this
with you right now.

13:34.660 --> 13:35.850
I'm sorry. Okay.

13:36.180 --> 13:37.700
Look at her.

13:38.540 --> 13:41.650
Yeah. Add mouth-catching
to things she can't do.

13:41.720 --> 13:43.850
No. I mean, she's not
nervous at all,

13:43.930 --> 13:45.880
and look at the other kids.
They're a wreck.

13:45.970 --> 13:47.250
You know, she may not have
gotten our talent,

13:47.370 --> 13:49.980
but she didn't get
our self-consciousness either.

13:50.960 --> 13:53.630
Oh. Well, we're not giving her
<i>our</i> self-consciousness.

13:53.740 --> 13:55.890
Today is her day,
and she is--

13:56.080 --> 13:58.060
She is gonna sing.
Come on.

13:58.180 --> 14:01.380
♪

14:04.640 --> 14:07.240
[ Amplified voice ]
Hi. My mom's doing chemo,

14:07.360 --> 14:10.020
so I shaved my head
to be like her.

14:10.130 --> 14:12.180
This is for you, mom.

14:13.060 --> 14:16.790
[ Voice belting ] ♪ and I ♪

14:16.880 --> 14:18.290
♪ I ♪

14:18.400 --> 14:22.300
♪ will always love you ♪

14:22.370 --> 14:24.510
♪ ooh, ooh ♪

14:24.590 --> 14:26.770
- Hey, hey, we got a problem.
- What's wrong, sweetie?

14:26.880 --> 14:28.950
I can't go after her.
Are you kidding?

14:29.750 --> 14:32.600
Okay, well, honey, we can't
just leave right now.

14:32.780 --> 14:36.310
Sorry, gotta run.
Maya's feeling a bit feverish.

14:36.400 --> 14:38.720
Oh, well, I guess some people
can't take the heat.

14:38.890 --> 14:42.430
♪ ...will always love you ♪

14:42.510 --> 14:44.080
- [ Under breath ] Can you believe that?
- No.

14:44.260 --> 14:46.390
Okay, now we can leave.
Let's go out the side door.

14:47.420 --> 14:48.880
Hey, dad, I--

14:49.460 --> 14:50.720
I tried to grab you
after the shoot,

14:50.810 --> 14:51.920
but you just flew out of there.

14:52.020 --> 14:52.990
I didn't want it to seem like

14:53.090 --> 14:54.940
I was hanging around
for compliments.

14:55.020 --> 14:57.310
There-- there was some
discussion after you left.

14:57.400 --> 14:59.520
- Keep it moving, buddy!
- Um...

14:59.640 --> 15:02.170
A-a few people feel that
you came across a little--

15:02.290 --> 15:04.800
Sign says "No Menus"!

15:05.840 --> 15:06.880
What'd you say?

15:06.960 --> 15:07.890
Uh...

15:08.050 --> 15:09.420
the group thinks

15:09.580 --> 15:11.500
that maybe it would be
for the best

15:11.590 --> 15:14.690
if-- if someone else
was our spokesman.

15:14.880 --> 15:16.790
It's called
Pritchett's Closets.

15:16.880 --> 15:18.500
Yeah, I know,
but you were coming off

15:18.590 --> 15:20.320
- just a tiny bit--
- Damn kids.

15:20.430 --> 15:21.330
It's mine now!

15:21.420 --> 15:23.450
- Tiny bit grumpy.
- Grumpy?

15:23.550 --> 15:24.860
There's nothing wrong
with being a little gruff.

15:24.950 --> 15:26.300
That's how you are.

15:26.390 --> 15:27.660
- But when it comes to selling, dad--
- What do you mean--

15:27.750 --> 15:29.240
what do you mean, how I am?

15:29.350 --> 15:31.330
Is that what people think of me,
that I'm some big grump?

15:31.460 --> 15:33.010
Dad, that cannot be a big shock

15:33.090 --> 15:34.950
- that kids call you "Grumpa."
- Since when?

15:35.070 --> 15:38.030
Not to your face?
Cowards.

15:38.130 --> 15:42.330
So if I get "Grumpa,"
what do they call Phil's dad?

15:42.450 --> 15:45.420
You know, just...
"Funpa."

15:45.490 --> 15:48.480
That mound of human silly string
gets "Funpa"?

15:48.570 --> 15:50.590
- That's not the issue, dad.
- No, no, I know what the issue is.

15:50.800 --> 15:52.740
You're saying I'm not
warm and cuddly enough

15:52.810 --> 15:54.290
to sell closets anymore.

15:54.420 --> 15:56.540
It's a day that every father
knows <i> may</i> come

15:56.700 --> 15:58.160
but hopes it never will.

15:58.270 --> 15:59.500
Are we sure every father--

15:59.580 --> 16:01.180
- Stop hurting me!
- Oh!

16:05.220 --> 16:07.980
Hey, how you feelin'?

16:08.460 --> 16:10.160
<i>Hey.</i>

16:10.360 --> 16:11.820
Oh, looks like they got you

16:11.900 --> 16:14.240
on a bunch of good drugs
before your surgery.

16:14.330 --> 16:16.870
[ Chuckles ] I just came in
to check on you.

16:16.960 --> 16:19.220
Pretty scary going through this
all by yourself.

16:19.350 --> 16:21.150
[ Mocking voice ]
Too bad your girlfriend

16:21.260 --> 16:22.850
couldn't be here.

16:22.940 --> 16:24.140
Beth <i> is</i> real.

16:24.220 --> 16:25.510
I know that.

16:25.620 --> 16:26.970
No.

16:27.300 --> 16:29.190
Beth <i> is</i> real.

16:29.280 --> 16:31.360
Okay, you really wanna
talk about it?

16:31.470 --> 16:33.630
How real is your relationship?

16:33.780 --> 16:36.810
Real is when someone finds out
that you're in the hospital

16:36.970 --> 16:39.530
and drops everything because
she doesn't want you

16:39.620 --> 16:41.760
to be freaked out and alone.

16:42.240 --> 16:44.520
Look, I'm not trying
to be mean.

16:44.610 --> 16:46.590
It's just...
You ever think you might be

16:46.700 --> 16:48.630
settling for something here?

16:49.850 --> 16:51.070
[ Sighs ]

16:51.630 --> 16:53.310
We've-- we've all done it.

16:53.590 --> 16:54.950
Talked ourselves
into the penguin

16:55.060 --> 16:57.690
because we didn't think
we had a shot at the elephant.

17:01.400 --> 17:03.170
[ Sighs ]

17:05.089 --> 17:07.710
If I'm your elephant,
you have a shot.

17:07.790 --> 17:09.630
That's what I'm trying
to say, dummy.

17:09.710 --> 17:11.440
[ Door opens ]

17:11.770 --> 17:13.260
I'm glad he's finally asleep.

17:13.390 --> 17:15.550
He kept going on
about Beth Israel Hospital.

17:15.640 --> 17:16.869
I told him his insurance
is fine.

17:16.950 --> 17:17.990
We can do the surgery here.

17:18.069 --> 17:20.339
Beth Israel? Oh.

17:20.540 --> 17:22.920
Oh, my God.
Andy, are you okay?

17:23.050 --> 17:23.790
He's okay, right?

17:23.890 --> 17:25.180
[ Whispers ]
Uh, yeah, he's sleeping.

17:25.270 --> 17:26.770
[ Whispers ]
Oh, thank God.

17:27.069 --> 17:28.740
I'm Beth, Andy's girlfriend.

17:28.830 --> 17:30.600
Oh. Hi. Uh, Haley.

17:30.690 --> 17:33.920
Of course. Andy's told me
so much about you.

17:33.990 --> 17:35.510
I'm so sorry about
missing the carnival.

17:35.590 --> 17:37.260
I've just been up
for two days straight.

17:37.450 --> 17:40.610
Well, you're here,
so I should go.

17:40.700 --> 17:42.140
Okay. Thanks again.

17:42.220 --> 17:43.240
Mm.

17:54.210 --> 17:55.210
Listen, listen.

17:55.310 --> 17:57.210
It worked.
He stopped crying.

17:57.290 --> 17:59.520
Oh, so good for him.
I'm glad. So listen.

17:59.630 --> 18:02.080
Who are these beautiful people?
They must be cousins of yours?

18:02.160 --> 18:03.950
- Yes, they are--
- Mm-hmm.

18:04.030 --> 18:05.410
Wait a minute.

18:05.580 --> 18:07.290
- You turned it off.
<i>- [ Joe crying ]</i>

18:07.380 --> 18:10.640
And I thought that he was
finally getting over his binky!

18:10.760 --> 18:13.120
The screaming
is driving me crazy!

18:13.190 --> 18:15.360
The screaming is driving
everyone crazy, Gloria.

18:15.480 --> 18:16.840
You either have to turn
this thing off,

18:16.930 --> 18:17.690
or I'm going up there

18:17.760 --> 18:19.550
and giving him my keys
to suck on.

18:19.650 --> 18:22.200
Hey-o!
How's my beautiful wife?

18:22.380 --> 18:24.800
What happened?
Why do you look like that?

18:24.880 --> 18:26.080
I'm just happy to see you.

18:26.170 --> 18:27.630
You look like a crazy person.

18:27.700 --> 18:29.090
Dad, what are you doing
with your face? Come on.

18:29.200 --> 18:31.470
Did anyone else notice
that Joe stopped crying? Aah.

18:31.570 --> 18:33.930
Back from the talent show early.
Don't ask why.

18:34.010 --> 18:35.250
I love it when children
have talent.

18:35.380 --> 18:36.580
Mitchell: Why are you
smiling like that?

18:36.670 --> 18:37.850
[ Gasps ] Did something
happen to mom?

18:37.960 --> 18:40.850
Put your face back
to what it used to be.

18:40.930 --> 18:42.160
Come on, dad.
Just drop it.

18:42.270 --> 18:45.370
So now I'm too happy.
Make up your damn minds!

18:45.680 --> 18:46.820
There he is.

18:47.710 --> 18:49.030
I've got it.

18:50.010 --> 18:51.140
[ Cap squeaks ]

18:52.410 --> 18:55.530
Dad, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to upset you.

18:55.630 --> 18:56.770
Save it, Claire.

18:57.510 --> 18:59.570
I watched what we shot today.

18:59.730 --> 19:01.450
- Mm-hmm.
- Yeah, I'm not that cheery,

19:01.570 --> 19:03.730
likeable celebrity I was
30 years ago.

19:04.440 --> 19:08.180
I am an old grump now.
When did I turn that corner?

19:08.320 --> 19:09.530
You haven't. You haven't.

19:09.610 --> 19:11.110
I mean, you're creeping
up to it.

19:11.180 --> 19:13.930
You got your blinker on,
but... you haven't yet.

19:14.010 --> 19:15.450
I saw it happen to my dad,
you know?

19:16.180 --> 19:19.060
One day, happy-go-lucky
rotary drill operator,

19:19.100 --> 19:21.460
the next he's throwing
his schlitz at the TV

19:21.560 --> 19:23.540
'cause some lady sportscaster
came on.

19:23.620 --> 19:24.870
[ Chuckles ]

19:25.030 --> 19:26.580
I swore I'd never be like that.

19:26.670 --> 19:28.040
You're not that bad.
If you were,

19:28.120 --> 19:30.250
why would we all spend
all our time over here?

19:30.330 --> 19:32.130
- Oh, you just come here for the pool.
- That's not...

19:32.230 --> 19:35.830
That's not true.
No. Crazy.

19:35.950 --> 19:37.650
[ Inhales and exhales deeply ]

19:37.750 --> 19:40.250
Dad, you are a long way
from turning into grandpa.

19:40.400 --> 19:41.950
You know, I was with him

19:42.080 --> 19:45.420
the first time he saw sushi
in the grocery store.

19:45.590 --> 19:47.210
He grabbed the price check mike

19:47.310 --> 19:49.860
and treated us all to a little
lecture on Pearl Harbor.

19:50.010 --> 19:52.550
You just have to fight it
a little.

19:52.640 --> 19:54.350
- I appreciate it, honey.
- Mm.

19:54.450 --> 19:57.670
I'm not sure some of this just
isn't natural order of things.

19:57.770 --> 19:58.890
[ Door opens ]

19:58.970 --> 20:02.130
Bogey at 10:00! Move it!
This is not a drill!

20:02.200 --> 20:03.610
<i>What?</i>

20:03.800 --> 20:05.540
- [ Drone whirring ]
- Gentlemen, on my count,

20:05.640 --> 20:07.590
let slip the dogs of war!

20:07.690 --> 20:09.440
8... 7...

20:09.520 --> 20:12.910
What the hell are you three
doing out here?!

20:13.220 --> 20:14.920
Now if we have a prayer
at this thing,

20:15.030 --> 20:18.030
we have to triangulate.
Phil, stay where you are.

20:18.110 --> 20:19.860
- Luke, by the tree. Give me
some of those oranges. - Here you go.

20:19.970 --> 20:21.770
Now let's go on <i> my</i> count,

20:21.890 --> 20:23.900
'cause nobody starts at 8.

20:24.040 --> 20:26.660
3... 2... 1.

20:26.790 --> 20:29.270
[ All yelling ]

20:29.340 --> 20:31.700
Get the hell off the space
above my lawn!

20:31.970 --> 20:35.830
- Ow!
- Take a look at this. Look at this.

20:35.930 --> 20:36.880
[ Laughter ]

20:37.190 --> 20:38.140
[ Bang ]

20:38.870 --> 20:40.150
Hey!

20:40.520 --> 20:42.220
[ Laughter ]
We did it!

20:42.600 --> 20:43.910
We did it!

20:44.070 --> 20:45.350
[ Laughter ]

20:46.140 --> 20:49.140
Drone 2, Idiots 1!
[ Laughs ]

20:49.460 --> 20:51.360
Some boys need a little help,

20:51.690 --> 20:53.240
but not all boys.

20:53.320 --> 20:56.250
[ Crying ]

20:57.000 --> 20:58.360
No binky.

21:02.300 --> 21:03.640
All right, dad,
we're ready for you.

21:03.730 --> 21:04.960
Just give us five minutes.

21:05.300 --> 21:07.170
Seems like a waste of time,
but go ahead.

21:07.730 --> 21:09.950
Closet, but no cigar.

21:10.040 --> 21:12.310
Why? Because we closet.

21:12.420 --> 21:14.360
I'll have what <i>she's</i> closet.

21:14.740 --> 21:15.820
[ As "Forrest Gump" ]
Mama always said

21:15.920 --> 21:18.140
life is like a box of closets.

21:18.230 --> 21:20.300
On your mark, get set, closet.

21:20.370 --> 21:23.880
[ Imitates announcer voice ]
<i>Let's</i> get ready to closet!

21:23.960 --> 21:27.190
[ As "Tony Montana" ]
Say hello to my little closet.

21:27.660 --> 21:29.740
Damn it. They're all good.
